    <Statements>
      <Statement>Represent scalar multiplication graphically by scaling vectors and possibly reversing their direction; perform scalar multiplication component-wise, e.g., as &lt;i&gt;c&lt;/i&gt;(&lt;i&gt;v&lt;/i&gt;&lt;sub&gt;&lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/sub&gt;, &lt;i&gt;v&lt;/i&gt;&lt;sub&gt;&lt;i&gt;y&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/sub&gt;) = (&lt;i&gt;cv&lt;/i&gt;&lt;sub&gt;&lt;i&gt;x&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/sub&gt;, &lt;i&gt;cv&lt;/i&gt;&lt;sub&gt;&lt;i&gt;y&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/sub&gt;).</Statement>
